Document: StreamPeerSocket
Path: godot/classes/class_streampeersocket.rst
Summary: Abstract base class defining common behavior for socket-based streams in Godot.

StreamPeerSocket is an abstract base class that defines common behavior for socket-based streams. It provides foundational functionality for network communication through sockets, serving as a parent class for specific implementation classes like TCP and UDP peers. This class handles core operations such as connecting to servers, accepting connections, and managing data transmission over network sockets.
